<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-428643/R-HSA-428643>
        a       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0008150> , <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "The SLC17 gene family encode proteins which are organic anion transporters. There are three distinct subfamilies within SLC17; vesicular glutamate transporters (VGLUT1-3 encoded by SLC17A7,6 and 8), type I Na+-coupled phosphate co-transporters (encoded by SLC17A1-4) and a proton-coupled sialic acid co-transporter (encoded by SLC17A5) (Reimer RJ and Edwards RH, 2004).<br><br>Two members of the SLC5 gene family encode carboxylate transporters, SMCT1 and SMCT2 (Ganapathy V et al, 2008)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Organic anion transport by SLC5/17/25 transporters" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2009-07-06" , "Reviewed: D'Eustachio, Peter, 2024-02-19" , "Reviewed: D'Eustachio, Peter, 2025-08-12" , "Reviewed: He, L, 2009-08-24" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2009-07-06" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
                "2026-02-02" ;
        <http://purl.org/pav/providedBy>
                "https://reactome.org" ;
        <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref>
                "R-HSA-428643" ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#narrower>
